# Cache headers for Cloudflare Pages / Netlify.
#
# "no-cache" does NOT mean "don't cache" — it means "cache it, but revalidate with
# me before reusing it". The host fingerprints each file (ETag); the browser asks
# "still current?" and normally gets a ~200-byte 304 Not Modified and reuses its
# copy. When a deploy changes a file its ETag changes, so the browser is handed the
# new version automatically. That's why there is no manual asset version to bump.
#
# ("no-store" is the one that disables caching entirely — not used here.)

/*
  Cache-Control: no-cache

# Data snapshots change only when the prep scripts are re-run, but revalidation is
# cheap (a 304) and guarantees a regenerated dataset is picked up, so same rule.
/data/*
  Cache-Control: no-cache

# Long-lived immutable assets could go here with max-age=31536000 if any are ever
# content-hashed in the filename (e.g. app.a1b2c3.js). None are today.
